<br>
So you can blame players like me for some of the changes in direction away from dungeons.<br>
<br>
DAoC also had a shift away from dungeons (somewhat naturally so because of the massive RvR aspect), with the Darkness Falls being a major exception.  But then, I still didn't quite get the point of having to go past masses of sometimes-aggressive greens to get to level-appropriate content, and going back with a green train when leaving.  As a soloist especially, outdoors is generally much more preferable to a dungeon that's generally scripted and meant for a certain group size.<br>
<br>
Of course, I'd enjoy a well-scripted dungeon crawl with a good group once in awhile -- I just don't want to be stuck there, and given one choice, would choose more outdoor zones instead. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ackar>Ackar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 600<br> <font color=#333333>(2/14/03 6:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8775.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Anyone else see something wrong with being in a dungeon?</span><hr size=1> What do people think of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>underwater</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> dungeons?<br>
