<br>
As for no good dungeons on Luclin--  Your just too high to appreciate them, try making a twink.<br>
<br>
Paludal Caverns.  XP, fair cash loot for the &lt;25 characters.  Fun set up, great underdark feel, shroomy goodness all 'round.<br>
<br>
Echo Caverns hidden side AKA Paludal 2.0--  One of my favorite dungeons in the game.  Mutants, Aliens, Giant Mosquitoes, and weird alien bloodsucking plants.  Merchants and bankers in the zone.  Abundant level appropriate loot with good stats, especially off named mutants.  Fun, and different fights--you can be turned into a mutant, you can fight the light damage super fast hitting needlites, Boglings are all around tough for their level.  XP, Loot, easy access-- this dungeon has it all.<br>
<br>
Netherbian Lair-- Something is amiss in there.  I kept waiting forever for the GM event to turn that place into a nightmare, because the Netherbians just seem like nightmare material that was never used.  Down side is crap loot and many adds. But, it's easy to traverse, fun to explore, and easy to get too.  Great dungeon if you like to crawl, you can go in and out of those tunnels all day.<br>
<br>
Go back to the levels where you can enjoy Sol A, Najena, Splitpaw and Dalnir's and you will be able to appreciate the dungeons of Luclin that aren't over run by Ubers. <p><br>
