I can't comment much on Droga/Nurga (Although one of them sucks because you can't get out the way you came in, can't remember which), but Sebilis was a good dungeon because itwas made like Guk.  Guk was a good dungeon because it was challenging, and had camp spots rather than this random crap Verant likes to implement.  Sol A is a great dungeon, but never really got much use because it was *too* difficult, the lava was a pain in the ass and the pathing was horrendous.  Sol B on the other hand was amazing again because of challenge (OMFG you actually need to split mobs instead of pulling them from a desert waste) and again, camp spots.  Kedge?  Kedge is and always will be the best dungeon in the game in my opinion.<br>
<br>
