<br>
Outdoor zones for their ease, use of horse and safety.<br>
<br>
Indoor zones for their exp bonuses, loot and excitement.<br>
<br>
Solo, I've done DL. I've done Stonebrunt. I've done Hole. I've done RM. I've done Paineel. And I've done Tower of Frozen Shadow.  Hehe, I even did elite ledge solo at level 13.  Each zone has a unique strategy and play style teaching me about game play.<br>
<br>
Stonebrunt taught me about pathing and aggro radius.  Hole taught me about pulling tough singles in a dungeon.  ToFS taught me about how to deal with an inevitable double, how to pull with Eye of Zomm and when to bail or when to burn mana.  DL... well... DL kind of sucked but at least I know how to get to KC now?<br>
<br>
What I'm saying is, don't skip over your lower level dungeons for EXP.  Many of them have an awesome bonus... in exp, gameplay experience and entertainment. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13790"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.rogers.com/shadowedblade/andarasig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2926<br> <font color=#333333>(2/17/03 7:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8775.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Underwater dungeons</span><hr size=1> I <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">love</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> hunting underwater, I hope they eventually open up the underwater zone that is clearly beneath <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Lake of Ill Manners</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I think that is supposed to be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Veksar</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
